</div>
</div>
</div><br />
<br />
As for what free game to pick, it's kind of funny, but the most well-regarded games this year are going to suffer from the same problems you (Solesk) might have with Fallout. They were large, sprawling open-worlds. Witcher 3, Metal Gear Solid 5, etc. Tomb Raider is the obvious stand out for a relatively linear and high quality experience. Looking over what's available, I really liked Batman: Arkham Knight.<br />
<br />
If you opt for the $60 Target gift card deal, instead of getting one single game you can get multiple cheaper games, including some they have on sale during the same time period. Arkham Knight or Witcher 3 for $25, Call of Duty Advanced Warfare, Battlefield Hardline, Dark Souls 2 for $20. Though this doesn't account for Tomb Raider.<br />
<br />
You are probably going to want Tomb Raider regardless of which bundle you pick, so it all boils down to different ways to save $50. Though if you are dead set on Kinect, you might not to want to trade the 360 in, as the $100 extra you will pay does not offset the $50 you save by trading it in. The 1TB is also a difference of $50.</div>

