			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>I didn't care for the original game.  It was OK, and was certainly disturbing at times, but these type of games just aren't my cup of tea.<br />
<br />
However, I absolutely love that the devs hid a scavenger hunt in the new release, and hid it from data miners by the way they went about it.  For those unfamiliar, here are the details (spoilers obv):<br />
<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_description">Quote:</div>
	<div class="bbcode_quote printable">
		<hr />
		
			INTRODUCTION<br />
<br />
When The Binding of Isaac: Rebirth released last year, a super-secret character called The Lost was included, with a complex unlocking mechanism that was designed to be a community scavenger hunt. However, dataminers quickly discovered his existence by looking at the game code and he became common knowledge within a few days, to the disappointment of the game creators.<br />
<br />
With the release of the Afterbirth expansion, there was a new secret, but this one was not so easily discovered. The final reward (The Keeper) was not patched into the game until the community solved the puzzle, and many puzzle elements were not in the game at all, requiring Twitter, voice mail, and even two real-world expeditions to solve. This sort of out-of-game puzzle is more generally known as an Alternate Reality Game, or ARG.
			
		<hr />
	</div>
</div>Full story here:<br />
<br />
<a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/bindingofisaac/comments/3ss8oo/the_afterbirth_arg_a_stepbystep_summary/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">https://www.reddit.com/r/bindingofis...ystep_summary/</a></div>

