			<title><![CDATA[November '15 Release Thread]]></title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?78231-November-15-Release-Thread&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Sat, 31 Oct 2015 01:54:25 GMT</pubDate>
			<description>This is it, the biggest month in the year for new game releases. Traditionally there are usually only a few games released this month, but each of these releases are so big that smaller games scramble to get out of their way (Call of Duty, chiefly). This year is a little different. There seem to be...</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>This is it, the biggest month in the year for new game releases. Traditionally there are usually only a few games released this month, but each of these releases are so big that smaller games scramble to get out of their way (Call of Duty, chiefly). This year is a little different. There seem to be more juggernauts this month than usual this year.<br />
<br />
This month is so packed that awarding a single title with &quot;biggest game of the month&quot; seems like an impossible task, but I'm going to award it to <b>Fallout 4</b> all the same. We have only technically known about this game for a few months, but even the announcement alone was one of the most hotly anticipated video game events of this year. Though I do have to say that I find it tremendously amusing that there has been this group of fans that have wanted a new Fallout more than anything else, but then when it finally gets announced a bunch of naysayers start chiming in and complaining that it looks too much like Fallout 3. That's what people wanted! <br />
<br />
<br />
Also big this month, <b>Call of Duty: Black Ops III</b>. This series has had a relatively rocky road with the past few releases, but all indications seem to suggest that this one is doing everything right. This might be the first year EA ever actually beats them though, as <b>Star Wars Battlefront</b> also comes out this month. A multiplayer shooter of the most authentic looking Star Wars game to date, right at the start of new movie fever? They would have to botch this release far worse than they have ever botched anything before to mess this up, which is entirely possible. Should be a close race, regardless.<br />
<br />
Not quite on the same level, the new <b>Need for Speed</b> also comes out this month. This one is attempting to combine the various things fans liked about previous entries in the series, modding, goofy FMV, etc.<br />
<br />
<br />
Once again, the Xbox gets the bigger exclusive this month, as they get early access to <b>Rise of the Tomb Raider</b>. I am personally leery of this game possibly being rushed to meet the holiday season, so would recommend waiting for impressions/reviews, but if it turns out right it should be pretty good. The PS4 meanwhile gets an expansion to <b>Bloodborne</b> titled <b>The Old Hunters</b>, and if you didn't get the original game you can get them together for less than price of the base game at launch. Good deal.<br />
<br />
Nothing huge for the Wii U this month, a new <b>Mario Tennis</b> and an Animal Crossing board game. Both the 3DS and the Wii U also get <b>Rodea the Sky Soldier</b>, which I honestly know nothing about, except that it is another one of those Japanese games that got a large swell of localization support from fans.<br />
<br />
<br />
On handhelds, the 3DS is having a pretty good month, with the biggest title arguably being <b>Yo-kai Watch</b>. This is basically Pokemon as made by Level 5 (Ni no Kuni). It's a monster rpg where you recruit various ghosts (yokai) to fill out your party. This was huge in Japan a few years ago, though I think it has died down a bit. The 3DS is also getting <b>Stella Glow</b>, a new strategy rpg from Imageepoch (sort of B tier) and a new <b>Pokemon Mystery dungeon</b>. <br />
<br />
The Vita meanwhile doesn't seem to be getting any significant new releases, unless you are a fan of Sword Art Online or live in Europe, in which case you finally get access to Persona 4 Dancing All Night, though I suspect fans probably just imported it.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Finally, the Protoss campaign of <b>Starcraft 2</b> finally comes out on PC this month. All of you waiting for the inevitable battlechest are one step closer to getting all three campaigns in one package. :p If you want to scratch a different kind of strategy itch, the latest <b>Anno</b> game is also supposed to come out this month.<br />
<br />
Edit: I have a correction. Apparently Blizzard is already bundling all three Starcraft campaigns for $60 if you buy it through Battlenet.<br />
