			<title>Paris Games Week - Sony Press Conference - New Trailers</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?78228-Paris-Games-Week-Sony-Press-Conference-New-Trailers&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Thu, 29 Oct 2015 23:09:55 GMT</pubDate>
			<description>Microsoft had a big Gamescom showing this year, whereas Sony did not. While my assumption was they would save all their post E3 announcements for their own event they hold in December, it turns out they decided to have a press event at Paris Games Week as well. I went into this not expecting much...</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>Microsoft had a big Gamescom showing this year, whereas Sony did not. While my assumption was they would save all their post E3 announcements for their own event they hold in December, it turns out they decided to have a press event at Paris Games Week as well. I went into this not expecting much at all, but it actually ended up being a pretty packed show. Much like the Microsoft briefing, I'm going to try to just focus on the highlights and gloss over the smaller stuff.<br />
<br />
<br />
The big new announcement was a new game from Quantic Dream, the makers of Heavy Rain. The new game is titled Detroid: Become Human, and is an evolution of a tech demo they created years ago about an android named Kara that had become sentient and didn't want to die. <br />
<br />
They also had a big gameplay demonstration of the previously announced Wild from Michel Ancel. In what they showed, you play as a shaman who communes with wildlife in order to accomplish your goals.<br />
<br />
They showed a slightly more in depth presentation of the Horizon Zero Dawn gameplay shown at E3, as well as a more in depth look at Media Molecule's weird &quot;Dreams&quot; game. They also announced a new Gran Turismo, as well as a few smaller titles.<br />
<br />
They had a big focus on promoting their upcoming Virtual Reality system, either showing or announcing support for several games, including an Until Dawn spinoff, Gran Turismo, Battlezone, etc.<br />
<br />
They showed trailers for, or talked about, a ridiculous number of games, so I'm not going to list them all. Here are a few examples: Bloodborne expansion, Uncharted multiplayer, Tekken 7, Battlefront,  No Man's Sky, Gravity Rush 2 (previously announced at Tokyo Game show), etc.</div>

]]></content:encoded>
